{
  "texts": [
    "Corpus on BlockchainLLMs' training heavily relies on substantial data, with modern corpora typically exceeding dozens of terabytes in volume [141].",
    "This characteristic is inherently misaligned with the constraints that blockchain systems are generally designed to address.",
    "Reconciling blockchain's limitations in throughput and data-handling capacity with the extensive data requirements of LLMs represents one of the most pressing challenges in BC4LLMs.",
    "Several approaches have explored the use of zero-knowledge proofs (ZKPs) to enhance scalability [118,103].",
    "However, relying on zero-knowledge technology solely for scalability, and not privacy, poses challenges due to the computational cost of generating ZKPs, even with minimal circuits."
  ]
}